org.jretrofit
Class Retrofit

java.lang.Object
  org.jretrofit.Retrofit

public final class Retrofit
extends java.lang.Object

This class has static shortcut methods to create retrofitted objects with the least possible amount of code. Equivalent methods are found on Retrofitter interface.

Author:
Ville Peurala

complete

public static <T> T complete(java.lang.Object target,
                             java.lang.Class<T> interfaceToImplement)
                  throws AllMethodsNotImplementedException
Make the target implement a single interface with a "complete" retrofitting, which means that the target must "implement" ALL methods specified on the given interface.

Parameters:
target - a target object.
interfaceToImplement - an interface to "implement".
Returns:
a retrofitted object which can be cast to the given interface.
Throws:
AllMethodsNotImplementedException - if the target object does not wholly "implement" the required interface.

Make the target implement multiple interfaces with a "complete" retrofitting, which means that the target must "implement" ALL methods specified on ALL of the given interfaces.

partial

public static <T> T partial(java.lang.Object target,
                            java.lang.Class<T> interfaceToImplement)
Make the target implement a single interface with a "partial" retrofitting, which means that it is not checked whether the target has all the required methods. Use this if you want to use just a subset of the methods defined on the interface.

Parameters:
target - a target object.
interfaceToImplement - an interface to "implement" partially.
Returns:
a retrofitted object which can be cast to the given interface.

withMethodLookupCaching

public static Retrofitter withMethodLookupCaching()
Returns a Retrofitter which caches method lookup, which means that retrofitted objects returned by it generally perform a lot faster than objects created by a non-caching retrofitter. Use this if you want speed.

Returns:
a caching Retrofitter implementation.

withoutMethodLookupCaching

public static Retrofitter withoutMethodLookupCaching()
Returns a Retrofitter which does not cache method lookup, which means that retrofitted objects returned by it generally perform a lot slower than objects created by a caching retrofitter. Use this if speed is not an issue.

Returns:
a non-caching Retrofitter implementation.
